        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>All imports were eliminated after overall consistency between DUL, SOSA/SSN, and POP was ascertained.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</subject>
              <property>http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Prescription, Observation, Prediction ontology</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</subject>
              <property>http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/description</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Ontology for Prescriptions (subclass of dul:Description), Observations, Predictions. Built on DUL, PROV-O, and SOSA/SSN. Also considers Specifications and Corrections (as subclasses of Prescriptions).

POPs and Current State of some Digital Twin (out of scope here) are formally similar, but epistemically quite different: POPs are facts, hence immutable. Facts can be erroneous or incomplete or obsolete, but remain as they were delivered or computed until they get discarded.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</subject>
              <property>http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/license</property>
              <object>
                <iri>https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/</iri>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>0.2: time dimension removed (expected to be handled with dul:Situation or similar). IRI refactoring and conceptual cleanup.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</subject>
              <property>http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/creator</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Airy Magnien</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language/>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop</subject>
              <property>http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/date</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>17 June 2026</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language/>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedQuality</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedQuality</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Asserted quality</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral</datatype>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedQuality</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>The externally defined property (NOT: PROPERTY VALUE) that AssertedQuality refers to shall be indicated using pop:aboutProperty, which is an owl:AnnotationProperty. pop:aboutProperty can target any rdf resource, such as a class, an object property, a data property, as long as that resource unambiguously defines what property is meant (from a domain point of view).</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedQuality</value>
        </iri>
        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedTimeInterval</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedTimeInterval</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>a sosa:resultTime is equivalent to a degenerated pop:AssertedInterval. In general, if the observation period is an interval, it will result in an AssertedInterval ending at the resultTime.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral</datatype>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedTimeInterval</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Asserted time interval</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral</datatype>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedValue</value>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedValue</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Asserted value</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral</datatype>
                <language/>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertedValue</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>The value (quality or quantity) and its uncertainty or tolerance, in most generic form.</lexicalForm>
                <datatype>http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral</datatype>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
        </iri>
        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rsm/pop/pop#AssertionGeneratingActivity</value>
          <annotations>
